learning_outcomes.en:
Upon successful completion of this course, students should:
*	have devised a written proposal for an MA thesis or MA project, laying out the topic, aims, theoretical and methodological starting points and time frame of the project/thesis;
*	be capable of explaining the relevance of the chosen topic and how the proposed thesis/project is linked to and different from other studies/projects on related topics;
*	be capable of analysing potential risks and problems, and opportunities to prevent them, and of finding ethical solutions;
*	be capable of charting their skills, knowledge and needs for personal professional development.

independent_work.et:
1) Smaller individual and group tasks;
2) Outline of MA thesis and oral presentation thereof: preliminary topic, aim, research questions, theoretical and methodological framework, timeline.

Guidelines will be given at the beginning and during the course.

description.et:
Oral presentation of the thesis outline
- ability to deliver one's ideas clearly;
- ability to answer questions from the audience.

Outline of the MA thesis including a preliminary formulation of the topic, aims and research questions, a preliminary overview of relevant theories and methods, and timeline.
- the topic, aims and research questions are succinctly formulated;
- theories and methods cited are relevant, the author understand them and is capable of explaining them;
- realistic timeline.

grade_preconditions.et:
1) Participation in classroom meetings and field trip(s);
2) Outline of MA thesis and oral presentation thereof.
3) Smaller practical individual and/or group assignments.

grade_evaluation.et:
1) Participation in weekly classroom meetings and field trips (preferably no missed classes!);
2) Punctual submission of coursework;
3) Outline of the MA thesis and oral presentation thereof.
